  "prompt": "Can i send my GRE scores to the four universities freely?",
  "response": "Yes, you can send your GRE scores to four universities for free as part of your GRE test registration. Here's how it works:\n\n### **Free Score Reports**\n- **Included Recipients:** When you register for the GRE, you are automatically entitled to send your official score reports to **four selected institutions or programs** at no additional cost.\n- **Selection Process:** During your registration, you'll have the option to choose these four institutions. If you decide to send scores after you've taken the test, you can do so through your ETS (Educational Testing Service) account.\n\n### **Sending Additional Score Reports**\n- **Extra Fees:** If you wish to send your scores to more than four institutions, you can do so for an additional fee per recipient. As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, the fee is typically around $27 per additional score report, but it's a good idea to check the current fees on the [ETS website](https://www.ets.org/gre/revised_general/prepare/scores/send) as they may change.\n  \n### **How to Send Scores**\n1. **During Registration:** Select up to four institutions to receive your scores automatically when you register.\n2. **After the Test:**\n   - **Log In:** Access your ETS account online.\n   - **Select Scores to Send:** Choose which additional institutions you'd like to send your scores to.\n   - **Pay Fees (if applicable):** Complete the payment for any additional score reports.\n\n### **Important Tips**\n- **Plan Ahead:** Make sure to identify the correct institutions and their specific codes to ensure your scores are sent to the right places.\n- **Deadlines:** Check the application deadlines for each university to ensure your scores arrive on time.\n- **Verification:** After sending, verify with the institutions to confirm they've received your scores.\n\nSending your GRE scores to four universities for free is straightforward and conveniently integrated into the GRE registration process. If you need to send them to more than four schools, ETS provides an easy way to do so for an additional fee.\n\nIf you have any specific questions or encounter issues while sending your scores, you can reach out to ETS customer service for assistance.",
